Advantages and Limitations of PCA

Discussed the strengths and limitations of Principal Component Analysis.

Advantages:

Reduces computational complexity.
Removes redundant features.
Reduces overfitting.
Improves model performance.
Simplifies visualization.
Handles correlated variables effectively.

Limitations:

Reduces interpretability of original features.
May lose some information.
Sensitive to feature scaling.
Assumes linear relationships among variables.
